cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.AR 

This paper is about improving the efficiency of deep learning applications, specifically during training, by exploiting dynamic sparsity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SIMD processors, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
